            <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
            <noteGrp type="publications">
               <note type="editions">An edition established by H S Nyberg in Kleinere Schriften
                     des Ibn al-ʿArabî, (Leiden, 1919). A recent critical edition, plus an Urdu
                     translation, published by The Ibn ʿArabī Foundation (Rawalpindi, Pakistan,
                     2014), edited by Abrār Aḥmad Shāhī. This is based upon the best early
                     manuscripts as found in the MIAS archive, including Yusuf Ağa 4859 and Koprulu
                     713, but not the autograph Leiden Or 86, which had not yet been identified when
                     the text was edited.</note>
               <note type="translations">English translation by Shaykh Tosun Bayrak: Divine
                     Governance of the Human Kingdom, plus ‘What the seeker needs’ and ‘Treatise on
                     Unity’, Louisville, 1997.</note>
